# Maintain Agent Documentation

When making **any** code or config change, update relevant documentation in the **same change** before finishing.

## Always update

- **docs/CHANGELOG.md** — add entry under `[Unreleased]` (what changed, concise)

## Update when applicable

| Change | Also update |
|--------|-------------|
| Module implemented or status change | docs/AGENT_GUIDE.md §3 implementation matrix |
| New/changed convention | AGENTS.md |
| Module behavior or design | docs/modules/<MODULE>.md |
| API shape (paths, schemas, contract) | docs/api/paths/, docs/api/schemas/, docs/api/API_CONTRACT.md |
| Setup commands or env vars | README.md, .env.example, deploy/env/application.env.example |
| Schema or partitions | alembic/versions/README.md, docs/reporting/sql/ if fact tables affected |
| Deploy / CI / infra | docs/deploy/CI_CD.md, deploy/README.md |
| Architecture / topology | docs/ARCHITECTURE.md |

## Rules

1. **Read actual code first** — docs must match implementation, not assumptions.
2. **Concise updates** — bullet or table row, not essays.
3. **Check OpenAPI vs main.py** before marking endpoints as implemented.
4. **No secrets** in documentation.
5. On release, move `[Unreleased]` items to a dated version section in CHANGELOG.

## Quick checklist

- [ ] CHANGELOG.md updated
- [ ] Status matrix updated if module/route status changed
- [ ] OpenAPI updated if API contract changed
- [ ] README/AGENTS.md if setup or conventions changed
